*** OAuth Access *** 
1. Link the client_secret.json file to the project roots directory

*** Installation *** 
1. Install go
$ brew install go

2. set the GOPATH variable to your working directory
$ export GOPATH = `pwd`

3. Create the necessary dirs for installation
$ mkdir src
$ mkdir pkg

4. Get the Gmail API Go client library, OAuth2, goquery
$ go get -u google.golang.org/api/gmail/v1
$ go get -u golang.org/x/oauth2/...
$ go get -u golang.org/x/net/html
$ go get github.com/PuerkitoBio/goquery

# Note: We could potentially skip this step if we checked in the src/ and pkg/ directory
#   It may be the case that we would expect this repository to live fully in the src/ directory but this
#   isn't what was suggested by this guide https://developers.google.com/gmail/api/quickstart/go


*** Exectuion *** 
$ go run main.go

*** Notes *** 
Emacs go-mode - https://github.com/dominikh/go-mode.el

